PING TEST AFTER DISCONNECTING A DEVICE FROM WI-FI

Objective:
Observe what happens when you try to ping a device that is no longer connected to the Wi-Fi network.

Steps:
1. Connect both the laptop and the other device (phone or another laptop) to the same Wi-Fi network.
2. Note the IP address of the other device.
3. Disconnect the other device from the Wi-Fi.
4. On the laptop, open Command Prompt.
5. Run:
   ping <device_IP_address>

Example:
   ping 192.168.1.105

Typical Error Message:

Request timed out.

Example Output:

Pinging 192.168.1.105 with 32 bytes of data:

Request timed out.
Request timed out.
Request timed out.
Request timed out.

